==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Greek]] '''[[ουτοπία]]''' (''ootopia'') "no (such) place", "[[utopia]]", a term coined by Sir Thomas More, from [[Ancient Greek]] prefix '''[[ου]]''' (''oo'') "not, no" + '''[[τόπος]]''' (''topos'') "place, region", metaph. "occasion, opportunity".

===Adjective===
'''utopian'''
# [[ideal]] but often [[impractical]]; [[visionary]]
